The paper deals with the problem of inferring an unknown graph using distance or shortest path queries between its vertices. This problem is closely related to graph algorithms and data structures, which are covered by cs.DS. The paper also involves analyzing the query complexity of algorithms, which falls under cs.CG (computational geometry) and cs.DM (discrete mathematics). The use of distance or shortest path queries suggests that the paper may involve graph theory, which is covered by cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.SI (social and information networks).
